data(indexes)
index_returns <- indexes[,1:5]

Run Optimization and Chart Results

Solvers

  • Close solvers (quadreatic programming) -> FAST / EXACT
  • Global solvers (differential evolution optimization) -> SLOWER / APPROXIATE

Quadratic Utility

Maximise: \(\mathbf{w}' \mathbf{\mu} - \lambda * \mathbf{w}' \mathbf{\Sigma}\mathbf{w}\) Subject to: - \(w_i \ge 0\) - \(\sum_{i=1}^N w_i = 1\)

Where: - \(\mathbf{w}\) is the weight vector - \(\mathbf{\mu}\) is the expected return vector - \(\lambda\) is the risk aversion parameter - \(\mathbf{\Sigma}\) is the variance - covariance matrix

Quadratic Programming Solver

package quadprog

solve.QP() solves problems in the form - \(min(-\mathbf{d}'\mathbf{b}+\frac{1}{2}\mathbf{b}'\mathbf{D}\mathbf{b})\)

subject to: - \(\mathbf{A}'\mathbf{b} \ge b_0\)

Portfolio specs, constraints and objectives

?portfolio.spec
?add.constraint
?add.objective

Optimization Methods
